article.description: Air Force pulls away from UC Riverside 62-52
article.headline: Air Force pulls away from UC Riverside 62-52
article.linkText: Air Force pulls away from UC Riverside 62-52
article.story: COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. -- Tre' Coggins scored 17 points to lead Air Force to the 62-52 victory over UC Riverside Saturday. Air Force (6-4) went into halftime with a 26-23 lead. Hayden Graham paced the Falcons, scoring seven points and pulling down six rebounds in the half. UC Riverside (3-5) trailed only by three despite struggles at the free-throw line, going 4 of 11 in the half. Air Force came out strong after the break, ripping off a 16-4 run and taking a 42-27 lead. Coggins scored nine points during the spurt. The Highlanders would cut the lead to seven after a Lucas Devenny three-point play, but a Kamryn Williams 3-pointer pushed the lead back to double figures with 2:23 left. UC Riverside never got closer than seven. Graham finished with nine points and a career-high eight boards. Taylor Johns paced UC Riverside, scoring 14 points and grabbing 12 rebounds.
